<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-11T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-11T04:00:00-05:00" n="302" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d302">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">762.94/76: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dickover</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-11T18:00:00+09:00">November
                                    11, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 11—7:11 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>231. Twice recently vernacular newspapers have published guarded
                            references to an unspecified but allegedly important diplomatic project
                            under consideration by the Government, the <hi rend="italic">Asahi</hi>
                            this morning stating that the matter will be submitted to the Privy
                            Council for approval. The submission of the matter to the Privy Council
                            suggests that an agreement which requires Imperial sanction is under
                            consideration, and credence is given in well-informed circles in Tokyo
                            to a report that the diplomatic project in question has to do with
                            Germany and that it is being opposed by the liberal group in the
                            Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dickover</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>